<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="308" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[1023,1821,1620,2190]" pageId="29" pageNumber="308">
Included in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1834" box="[1333,1542,1779,1818]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="308" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="megaphyllus">
<emphasis box="[1333,1542,1779,1818]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="308">megaphyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group; previously treated under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1905" box="[1524,1742,1831,1870]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="308" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="celebensis">
<emphasis box="[1524,1742,1831,1870]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="308">R celebensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but recendy classified as a distinct species based on limited morphological data, although more substantial studies are needed to confirm this. The taxon 
<emphasis box="[1620,1744,2044,2083]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="308">parvus</emphasis>
was previously included in this species but is 
<emphasis box="[1027,1106,2150,2189]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="308">now</emphasis>
regarded as a subspecies of 
<emphasis box="[1630,1819,2150,2190]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1871" box="[1630,1814,2150,2190]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinolophidae" genus="Rhinolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="308" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="keyensis">R keyensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[205,1826,2207,3456]" box="[206,416,2207,2246]" pageId="29" pageNumber="308">Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
